 <p>The US shoe sizing system uses different scales for men's and women's s=
izes. The general rule is 1.5 to 2 sizes difference in length and 1 full si=
ze difference in width between men's and women's shoe sizes. Below is a cal=
culator to input your shoe size and width to convert to the sizing equivale=
nt of opposite gender sizing.</p>
<p>NOTE: The conversion may vary slightly between different shoe brands and=
 styles, so it's advisable to refer to specific brand sizing charts for acc=
urate information. Additionally, the width options provide variations to ac=
commodate different foot shapes and sizes within each gender category.</p>
